==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Protophyte
<hw>Pro"to*phyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Proto-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a plant.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Any unicellular plant, or plant forming only a plasmodium, having
reproduction only by fission, gemmation, or cell division.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The protophytes (<class>Protophyta</class>) are by some
botanists considered an independent branch or class of the vegetable
kingdom, and made to include the lowest forms of both fungi and alg⟦ae⟧,
as slime molds, Bacteria, the nostocs, etc. Cf. <er>Carpophyte</er>, and
<er>Oophyte</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protophytology</ent>⟦br⟧
